comments.body:
Based on my understanding of the loop and the corresponding error thrown on line 1872, the `first` here refers to `no_key_parsed` bool that's initialised to `true` at the beginning and toggled to `false` when one is (possibly) parsed.
I think explicit variable naming like suggested above would help to read the code. An alternative (my preference) would be to use an `any_key_parsed` bool with inverse boolean values instead.


```cpp
        bool any_key_parsed = false;
        size_t max_providers_len = 0;
        while (expr.size()) {
            if (any_key_parsed && !Const(",", expr)) {
                error = strprintf("musig(): expected ',', got '%c'", expr[0]);
                return {};
            }
            any_key_parsed = true;
```

```cpp
        if (!any_key_parsed) {
            error = "musig(): Must contain key expressions";
            return {};
        }
```

